Moreover, the necessity to combat food waste across the supply chain is propelling the adoption of post-harvest treatments. These treatments play a pivotal role in preserving produce quality during storage, transportation, and distribution, ultimately reducing spoilage and losses. By leveraging innovative post-harvest solutions, producers and distributors can improve efficiency in maintaining the quality and freshness of fruits and vegetables, ensuring a higher percentage of harvest reaches consumers in optimal condition.

